  "texts": [
    "Here we explain a standard method in optimization, in which some of the constraints can be softened, which means we allow them to be somewhat violated, if needed.",
    "In optimization, softness refers to how much we care about different values of an objective.",
    "We can think of the objective as infinitely soft: We will accept any objective value, but we prefer larger values (if we are maximizing).",
    "We can think of constraints as infinitely hard: We will not accept any violation of them, even if it is only by a small amount.",
    "Soft constraints, described below, are in between."
  ],
